helpTexts.longDescription: Please ensure this field is populated for any linked deal (within or outside your product area). The linked product partner will be able to provide the deal ID and it's Deal Owner will receive a notification to advise them of the linking.
Please provide justification for adding Wall Crosser to the Deal Team.This information is mandatory for Control Room Validation if this is a Reportable Transaction.
The person(s) in  the Deal Team who is designated as the main contact point for Control Room in relation to any queries, or updates required.

- Deal Team Leader - The senior CF staff member(s) with overall responsibility and accountability for The Deal.- Deal Team member - People who are part of The Deal Team and are actively involved in The execution of The Deal.- Insider - Other staff from The Private Side who are aware of The Deal and who are not Above The Wall or auto-tagged for The relevant business.- Wall Crosser - staff from The Public Side (e.g. TB, FM, Research, Private Banking or Retail), who are brought into a Deal for a specific purpose.B46
Total size of the deal. In case of an Asset Sale, this is the purchase price of the Asset.
Date at which internal Loan will be Prepaid to ALM following Sale
Loan Capital prepayment to ALM as a result of Asset Sales
RWA Reduction resulting from Asset Sales
Asset Value at time of Sale

helpTexts.shortDescription: Current Year Loss in Lease Rentals
helpTexts.longDescription: Lease Rentals loss as a result of selling asset.
Depreciation Cost saving as a result of selling asset.
Any additional cash received (separate from Profits). These could be later used for Dividends.

helpTexts.shortDescription: Profit on Sale, Net of Transaction Costs
helpTexts.longDescription: Profit made on disposal of the asset, net of any transaction costs incurred
Indicate if deal is an Islamic Product
This is where the largest amount of the loan will be booked.
This is auto-calculated based on 'Expected Drawdown 1- Hold Amount (USD)' x 'RW (%)'
This is the first expected drawdown of the transaction.
Please include description of multiple tranches, drawdowns etc. In case of an Asset Sale, please include details of the sale.
Please input years to final maturity (from drawdown date)
This is SCB's share of the Deal Size. If the Funding Arrangement is 'Bilateral', then Total Deal Size should equal Hold Amount.
If 'Syndicated', ensure Syndications team is involved latest by 'Mandated' deal stage
Total fees expected on this deal (not limited to a year), including fees on any asset sales.
The margin over cost of funds (inclusive of liquidity premium), as charged to the client. This is not the NII(%) - the NII(%) would be calculated as Gross/ Client Margin(%) less Liquidity Premium(%)
All fees expected in current calendar year, including fees on asset sales.
Please include regular updates of the deal as it progresses, including the dates these changes happen.
The Expected/ Actual close date should be when the facility is signed, and not the drawdown date.
This is the probability of the deal completing at all, and is not an indication of timing, i.e. when the deal will close.
"Dormant" only means a deal is inactive, not that the deal is dropped/lost.If the deal is dropped/lost, update the 'Deal Stage' field."
'Mandated / Under Execution' can include both verbal and written mandates. If verbal, please mention this in the 'Deal Comments/ Updates' field.
Top-tier and Lower tier to be selected based on SCB's role in the transaction (For example 'Mandated Lead Arranger = Top-tier role).
Please ensure the exact entity being mandated is selected here, and not any entity in the same country.
Please select 'Joint' if SCB is not the only party advising/ lending to the client in this transaction.
Please provide a short summary of the transaction. This will be used for other activities you launch (eg: PSR form).
Please ensure this is a unique deal/project name, i.e. not currently used by another deal. Project names to be used for projects.
These are other locations involved in the deal execution.

This is the location for which the main deal execution work is done. This does not automatically mean where the deal team is located or a location where there is a Corporate Finance presence. Generally this should mirror where the maximum fees are booked or the mandate location.

Please add any additional clients involved in the same deal. Note these should be Clients, and not Counterparties in the deal. It is not required to tag the client group if they are not directly involved in the deal.
Please check that the GICs are issued for all locations involved (client, deal, fee/loan booking, etc.), else this transaction cannot be processed.
The status should be "Active", before you can progress the deal to 'Mandated' stage. Please contact your PFAM to onboard the client if is status is other than "Active"
Please select the PFAM directly involved with this transaction.

The correct client entity must be tagged before the deal moves to "Mandated" or "Completed" stage. Select the "Re-tag Deal" option on the top right to change to another client entity within the same Group.
Select this option for notification when the linked Deal changes Sales/Deal Stage
Comments entered here will be included in the notification that's sent to the Deal Owner of the deal you are linking to
